<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2006-04-07.S2W-23883.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-06/wa0407.htm#3">Roads</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2006-04-07.S2W-23883.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80095" speakername="Alex Neil (Central Scotland) (SNP)" spid="S2W-23883" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-06/wa0407.htm#3">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive how the construction of the new A8000 to M9 link road will be funded.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2006-04-07.S2W-23883.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80109" speakername="Tavish Scott" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-06/wa0407.htm#3">

  <p>Funding of the route upgrade is a matter for the Forth Estuary Transport Authority in the first instance. However, we are committed to underwriting the costs of the upgrade of the A8000-M9 Spur, to a maximum of &pound;24 million over three years.</p>

</reply>
